00193 //#define MAX_SORTING_LIMIT        20000
00194 /* Sorting of matches will not be performed if there are more than
00195    MAX_SORTING_LIMIT matches. This is to prevent bad behavior in the
00196    case of some unlucky inprecise search requests.
00197 
00198    If MAX_SORTING_LIMIT = MAX_EXTRACT_NBR_MATCHES, sorting will not be
00199    performed in the worst case, since we use two extractMatches(...)
00200    -> MAX_EXTRACT_NBR_MATCHES+1 is the total maximum of matches.
00201 */
00202 const uint32 MaxExtractNbrMatches = 35000;
00203 //#define MAX_EXTRACT_NBR_MATCHES  20000
00204 // XXX should be 2000.

00226 inline const char* 
00227 SearchTypes::getMatchingString( StringMatching matching ) {
00228    switch ( matching ) {
00229       case SearchTypes::ExactMatch:
00230          return "EM";
00231       case SearchTypes::CloseMatch:
00232          return "CM";
00233       case SearchTypes::FullMatch:
00234          return "FM";
00235       case SearchTypes::CloseFullMatch:
00236          return "CFM";
00237       case SearchTypes::WildcardMatch:
00238          return "WM";
00239       case SearchTypes::AllWordsMatch:
00240          return "AM";
00241       case SearchTypes::SoundexMatch:
00242          return "SM";
00243       case SearchTypes::EditDistanceMatch:
00244          return "EDM";
00245       case SearchTypes::MaxDefinedMatching:
00246          return "";      
00247    }
00248    return "WTF";
00249 }
